Project Description

This project is an HTML exercise composed of multiple interconnected index and HTML files.
All pages are linked together to create an interactive story experience.

The user (or tester) can choose different paths throughout the story.
Depending on the decisions made, the story will branch into different scenarios, leading to multiple possible endings.

Each choice affects the direction of the narrative, creating a unique experience every time the story is played.

Story Context

The story is based on two main characters:

Felipiño the Kid

Fausto the Older Brother

The world is set in a post-apocalyptic future where humanity has collapsed.
Half of the population disappeared due to a devastating global epidemic.

The survivors now struggle to stay alive in a dangerous environment where resources are scarce. People fight each other for food, fuel, and safe shelter. In this world, encountering another person can be just as dangerous as starving.

Felipiño and Fausto are the only survivors of their family.
They have been alone for six months after losing everyone they loved.

They were living in a relatively peaceful area until a violent gang arrived, trying to take control of all surrounding territories. This forces the two brothers to abandon their home and search for a new place to live.

This is where the interactive story begins.

Possible Endings

Depending on the choices made by the user, the story can end in several different ways:

They successfully find a safe place to live and start a new life.

They are killed by a wild bear.

They freeze to death due to extreme cold.

They die after eating a poisonous mushroom.

A mysterious dog appears and sends them back in time, allowing the player to restart the story from the beginning.